---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import FAQ from '../../../components/FAQ.astro';
import { articleSchema, breadcrumbSchema, faqSchema } from '../../../lib/schema';

const title = 'Cheap Ride-On Lawn Mowers Under £2,000 UK 2026';
const description = 'Budget ride-on mowers under £2,000 for UK lawns. We find the best value options for large gardens from specs and verified owner reviews.';
const path = '/ride-on-lawn-mowers/cheap/';
const datePublished = '2026-05-10';

const crumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Ride-on lawn mowers', url: '/ride-on-lawn-mowers/' },
  { name: 'Cheap', url: path },
];

const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'Can you get a decent ride-on mower for under £2,000?',
    a: 'Yes, but you\'re looking at smaller decks (76-84 cm), manual transmission (not hydrostatic), and basic engines. For a lawn under 2,500 m² on mostly flat ground, that\'s perfectly adequate. Avoid anything under £1,200 - the build quality drops sharply.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is a cheap ride-on better than an expensive push mower?',
    a: 'If your lawn is over 1,000 m², yes. A £1,500 ride-on will mow 2,000 m² in 30 minutes. Even a £600 self-propelled petrol mower takes 90+ minutes on the same area. The time saving alone justifies the price difference.',
  },
];

const schema = [
  breadcrumbSchema(crumbs),
  articleSchema({ headline: title, description, url: path, datePublished }),
  faqSchema(faqs),
].filter(Boolean);
---
<BaseLayout {title} {description} schema={schema}>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <Breadcrumbs items={crumbs} />

    <header class="mb-8">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-grass-700 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Budget Guide · Updated May 2026</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-soil-900 leading-tight">Cheap Ride-On Mowers Under £2,000</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        You don't need to spend £3,000+ to sit down while you mow. There are genuine options under £2,000 - you just need to know where the compromises are.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose-mowers">
      <h2>What you sacrifice under £2,000</h2>
      <p>
        At this price, expect a transmatic (manual gear) transmission rather than smooth hydrostatic, a smaller deck (76-84 cm vs 98-107 cm on premium models), and a less powerful engine. Build quality is adequate but not tank-grade - plastics where premium mowers use steel, and paint that chips easier. None of that stops it mowing, though.
      </p>

      <h2>Three budget ride-on mowers worth considering</h2>

      <h3>1. Stiga Estate 384M (£1,999)</h3>
      <p>
        Right at the budget ceiling but the best value ride-on in the UK. 84 cm deck, rear collector included, and a Stiga engine that's proven reliable. Handles lawns up to 2,500 m². <a href="/reviews/stiga-estate-384m/" class="text-grass-700 underline">Read our Stiga review</a> <a href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/s?k=stiga+estate+384m+lawn+mower&amp;tag=thebestmowers-21" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="text-grass-700 underline whitespace-nowrap">Check price &rarr;</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>2. McCulloch M115-77T (£1,499)</h3>
      <p>
        McCulloch (owned by Husqvarna) offers a 77 cm side-discharge deck, Briggs &amp; Stratton engine and transmatic drive for well under £2,000. No frills, but it mows large flat lawns reliably. <a href="/reviews/mcculloch-mht-5622/" class="text-grass-700 underline">Read our McCulloch review</a> <a href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/s?k=mcculloch+mht+5622+lawn+mower&amp;tag=thebestmowers-21" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="text-grass-700 underline whitespace-nowrap">Check price &rarr;</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>3. Mountfield 1330M (£1,699)</h3>
      <p>
        Mountfield's entry-level ride-on has an 84 cm deck, rear collection and a Mountfield-branded engine. Available at most UK garden centres with easy access to parts and servicing. A safe, boring, reliable choice - which is exactly what you want from a budget ride-on.
      </p>

      <h2>Second-hand is worth considering</h2>
      <p>
        A 3-5 year old John Deere or Husqvarna in good condition will outperform a brand-new budget ride-on for the same money. Check the engine hours (under 300 is good), inspect the deck for rust, and make sure the blades are straight. Dealers often sell refurbished units with a 12-month warranty.
      </p>
    </div>

    <FAQ {faqs} />
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
